linkedview.SB1Description3: The damage percent for each asset type is described by a probability distribution (QTs) defined by the flood depth (0.5, 1.0, 1.5, 2.0, 2.5) and the percent of asset damage (the matrix numbers).
linkedview.SB1MathExpression3: I3.Q1.distribtype + I3.Q2.5year + I3.Q3.10year + I3.Q4.25year + I3.Q5.50year + I3.Q6.100year
linkedview.SB1Description4: The damages for each asset type is described by a probability distribution (QTs) defined by the event probability (20, 10, 4, 2, 1) and the total damages (the matrix numbers).
linkedview.SB1MathExpression4: I4.Q1.distribtype + I4.Q2.5year + I4.Q3.10year + I4.Q4.25year + I4.Q5.50year + I4.Q6.100year+ I4.Q7.quantity
linkedview.SB1Description5: The cost for each project alternative is described as the probability of average annual costs (QTs).
linkedview.SB1Description6: The Math Results from Indicator 4 define average annual benefits and the Math Results from Indicator 5 defines average annual costs. Benefits are defined as the reduction in damages of each project alternative in comparison to the baseline.
